The ‘Zizojika Izinto’ campaign is in the Free State for safer festive season Police operations. Police Minister, Bheki Cele is visiting the province in an effort to strengthen the fight against crime. Cross-border crimes have been a major concern in the Free State, with many foreign nationals being arrested for various crimes especially in Lejweleputswa district. During the release of crime statistics in the province this year, it was revealed that more than sixty police officials were dismissed for alleged involvement in crime activities. The Police minister is engaging the community and inspecting police operations in Bloemfontein. 